# WordPress Simple Forum XML Generator

## This file generates a valid XML file of the Simple Forum Database.

Instructions:

1. Install SilverStripe v 2.4+. Note: once this is successfully installed, all necessary server configurations will have been installed.
http://doc.silverstripe.org/sapphire/en/installation/

2. Download and unzip the SimpleForum Exporter Module into the root directory of your SilverStripe Instalation
https://github.com/emelleme/SimpleForum-Exporter/zipball/master

3. Open the _config.php file in the SimpleForum Exporter directory you just unzipped, and set the database information for the Simple Forum Database.

4. Generate the xml. Navigate to <your silverstripe domain>/sfxml.xml The XML file will be generated.
(e.g. localhost/mysilverstripe/sfxml.xml)
Note: This module uses the default name scheme for the wordpress simpleforum tables. If you have modified the table names, update the SFImporter.php file.
see: http://wiki.simple-press.com/plugin-api/database-structure/
